snippet.textDisplay: Seth, I was watching one of your older videos about hacks and I thought you might like one of mine. Instead of those yolks you can buy for the workshop to hold your bars still while you work on the forks etc, you can use an innertube, I find 700C best. Cut all the way through an inch to either side of the valve and remove that section, you're left with a long rubber tube. Slip one end over your bar end, run it behind your seatpost then back to the other bar, cut to length so it's tight then slip that one over too. Holds them tight enough to work on your front end and unlike the shop bought ones you can turn the bars if you want and it'll maintain that angle. Great videos dude, shout me out if you use this in your next hacks vid =D
